FT  07 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Yorkshire Cable
Yesterday it was reported that Generale des Eaux, Singapore Telecom and
Yorkshire Water were to invest Pounds 200m in Yorkshire Cable. The companies
wish to make clear that their total investment over the next 10 years will
be Pounds 500m. In addition to Pounds 200m of equity, they plan to invest
Pounds 300m raised through borrowing and cash flow.
